<title>USA: Platinum Technology Inc Q4 loss narrows.</title>
<headline>Platinum Technology Inc Q4 loss narrows.</headline>
<dateline>OAKBROOK TERRACE, Ill. 1997-02-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Platinum Technology Inc</p>
<p>	     (In thousands, except per share amounts)</p>
<p>			   Q4 ended Dec 31	 Year ended Dec 31</p>
<p>			   1996	 1995  *    1996	  1995 *</p>
<p> Total revenue	142,804     98,033     439,190    304,676</p>
<p>Total costs and expenses</p>
<p>			  172,215    167,139     521,683    432,838</p>
<p> Operating loss    (29,411)   (69,106)    (82,493)  (128,162)</p>
<p> Other income	   2,590	1,290	 5,156	4,281</p>
<p>Loss before income taxes</p>
<p>			 (26,821)   (67,816)    (77,337)  (123,881)</p>
<p> Income Taxes	   3,153	(944)     (9,375)   (11,948)</p>
<p> Net loss	  ( 29,974)  ( 66,872)   ( 67,962)  ( 111,933)</p>
<p>Net loss per share</p>
<p>			  ( 0.53)    ( 1.31)     ( 1.22)    ( 2.59)</p>
<p>Shares used in computing</p>
<p>net loss per share</p>
<p>			   56,419     51,032	55,564     43,267</p>
<p>NOTE: Results for the three and twelve months ended December 31, 1995 are restated for mergers accounted for using the pooling-of-interests method of accounting.</p>
<p>After-tax charges of $37.4 million or 66 cents per share, for merger costs and acquired in-process technology brought the net loss for the fourth quarter of 1996 to $30.0 million, or $0.53 per share.</p>
<p>The net loss for the year ended December 31, 1996, was $68.0 million, or $1.22 per share, including the after-tax charges of $52.8 million, or $0.95 per share, for merger costs and acquired in-process technology.</p>
